theorem clopen_of_closure_eq_interior {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] {A : Set X} :
    closure (A : Set X) = interior (A : Set X) →
      IsOpen (A : Set X) ∧ IsClosed (A : Set X) := by
  intro hEq
  -- First, show `A = interior A`.
  have hA_eq_int : (A : Set X) = interior (A : Set X) := by
    apply Set.Subset.antisymm
    · -- `A ⊆ interior A`
      have h : (A : Set X) ⊆ closure (A : Set X) := subset_closure
      simpa [hEq] using h
    · -- `interior A ⊆ A`
      exact interior_subset
  -- Hence `A` is open.
  have hOpen : IsOpen (A : Set X) := by
    simpa [hA_eq_int] using isOpen_interior
  -- Next, show `A = closure A`.
  have hA_eq_cl : (A : Set X) = closure (A : Set X) := by
    apply Set.Subset.antisymm
    · exact subset_closure
    · -- Use `hEq` and `interior A ⊆ A`.
      have h_sub : interior (A : Set X) ⊆ (A : Set X) := interior_subset
      simpa [hEq] using h_sub
  -- Hence `A` is closed.
  have hClosed : IsClosed (A : Set X) := by
    simpa [hA_eq_cl] using
      (isClosed_closure : IsClosed (closure (A : Set X)))
  exact And.intro hOpen hClosed

theorem isOpen_of_isClosed_and_P1 {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] {A : Set X}
    (hA_closed : IsClosed (A : Set X)) (hP1 : Topology.P1 (A : Set X)) :
    IsOpen (A : Set X) := by
  -- First, show `closure (interior A) = A`.
  have hEq : closure (interior (A : Set X)) = A := by
    apply Set.Subset.antisymm
    · -- `closure (interior A) ⊆ A` because `A` is closed.
      have h₁ : closure (interior (A : Set X)) ⊆ closure (A : Set X) :=
        closure_mono (interior_subset (s := A))
      simpa [hA_closed.closure_eq] using h₁
    · -- `A ⊆ closure (interior A)` follows from `P1`.
      exact hP1
  -- Use the equality to deduce that `A` is open.
  exact isOpen_of_closure_interior_eq (A := A) hEq

theorem P1_nested_interior_closure {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] (A : Set X) :
    Topology.P1 (interior (closure (interior (closure (interior (A : Set X)))))) := by
  -- The set under consideration is an interior, hence open.
  have hOpen :
      IsOpen (interior (closure (interior (closure (interior A))))) :=
    isOpen_interior
  -- Any open set satisfies `P1`.
  simpa using
    (Topology.P1_of_isOpen
      (A := interior (closure (interior (closure (interior A))))) hOpen)
